applyAllowlistedSelectorsUpdates.t.sol
├─ when the caller does not have the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE
│  └─ it should revert
└─ when the caller has the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE
   ├─ when the workflow ID is not allowlisted
   │  └─ it should revert
   └─ when the workflow ID is allowlisted
      ├─ when the target is not allowlisted for the workflow ID
      │  └─ it should revert
      └─ when the target is allowlisted for the workflow ID
         ├─ when both removes and adds are empty
         │  └─ it should revert
         └─ when either removes or adds are not empty
            ├─ when a removed selector is not allowlisted
            │  └─ it should revert
            ├─ when an added selector is zero
            │  └─ it should revert
            ├─ when only removing selectors
            │  ├─ it should remove the selectors from the allowlist
            │  └─ it should emit the correct events
            ├─ when only adding selectors
            │  ├─ it should allowlist the selectors
            │  └─ it should emit the correct events
            └─ when adding and removing selectors in the same call
               ├─ it should process removes before adds
               ├─ it should correctly reflect the final allowlisted state
               └─ it should emit the correct events
